wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ap_compounding_pharmacist_nt_130313_wg1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-392\" src=\"http://ppcs-rx.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ap_compounding_pharmacist_nt_130313_wg1-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"ap_compounding_pharmacist_nt_130313_wg1\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>Training:</strong> pharmacy schools place very different emphasis on teaching their Future Pharmacists how to compound. In fact, a number of pharmacy schools do not even have a laboratory facility, so their students never practice this artful science before they graduate.\r\n\r\n<strong>Licensure exams:</strong> vary by state, and all but a handful of states have eliminated the compounding portion of their licensure exams. This explains the decrease in teaching compounding in pharmacy schools, but also eliminates any standards of basic competence in compounding for state licensure.\r\n\r\n<strong>Equipment:</strong> since not every pharmacy performs compounding, state pharmacy laws only require any pharmacy to keep the most basic (and often outdated) equipment on-hand. Having such antiquated equipment in the pharmacy simply meets the legal requirement, but does not imply that it can be used appropriately and accurately, nor that it is the best equipment for the task.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ppcs-rx.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/chem_lab_591.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-394\" src=\"http://ppcs-rx.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/chem_lab_591-300x188.jpg\" alt=\"chem_lab_591\" width=\"300\" height=\"188\" /></a>Quality Control and Assurance: most state pharmacy laws do not require pharmacies to test their non-sterile compounded preparations for potency to determine how accurately the dose of the compounded medication matches the prescribed dose. The facility should have rigorous quality assurance (QA) and quality control (QC) programs that include such potency tests, as well as procedures to identify and remedy any errors.','About Us','[block id=\"about-us-banner\"]','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2015-04-05 05:23:57','2015-04-05 05:23:57','',0,'http://skillons.com/?page_id=6',0,'page','',0),(262,1,'2015-01-06 16:40:00','2015-01-06 16:40:00','Would you like to transfer your prescription services to <span class=\"comp\">Atlantic Pharmacy and Compounding</span>? You may do so by filling out and submitting our Transfer RX form below and we will immediately process your request.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[row style=\"boxed\"]\r\n\r\n[col span=\"1/2\" ]\r\n<h3>Need Assistance?</h3>\r\n[divider width=\"full-width\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Phone</strong>: <a title=\"Telephone\" href=\"tel:3054000387\" data-rel=\"external\">305-400-0387</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Fax</strong>: <a title=\"Fax\" href=\"tel:3054377619\" data-rel=\"external\">305-437-7619 </a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Email</strong>: <a href=\"mailto:info@ppcs.com\">info@ppcs.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Monday - Friday</strong>\r\n8.00am - 5.00pm EST\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n[col span=\"1/2\" ]\r\n[ninja_forms id=7]\r\n\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Transfer Your RX','[block id=\"transfer-rx-banner\"]','publish','closed','closed','','transfer-your-rx','','','2015-03-27 04:43:25','2015-03-27 04:43:25','',0,'http://skillons.com/?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(263,1,'2015-01-06 16:40:38','2015-01-06 16:40:38','Here is a detailed response to some of the most frequently asked questions as <span class=\"comp\">Atlantic Pharmacy and Compounding</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Here is a detailed response to some of the most frequently asked questions as <span class=\"comp\">Atlantic Pharmacy and Compounding</span>\"]\r\n[accordion-item title=\"What is compounding?\"]\r\nCompounding pharmacy is the art and science of creating customized medicine for each patient. Compounding is a specialized skill with the potential to help many patients who could benefit from a more personalized medication. Pharmacists whospecialize in compounding l